<article index="true">
    <topic>
        <title>&lt;GroupBox&gt;</title>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <b>&lt;GroupBox/&gt;</b>
                    <ul>
                        <li><b>C++/Workflow</b>: (vl::)presentation::controls::GuiControl*</li>
                        <li><b>Template Tag</b>: &lt;ControlTemplate/&gt;</li>
                        <li><b>Template Name</b>: GroupBox</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            In the default control template,
            a <b>&lt;GroupBox/&gt;</b> is a container with a border and a label.
            Content of the label comes from the <b>Text</b> property.
        </p>
        <p>
            <b>&lt;GroupBox/&gt;</b> does not provide anything more than a <b>GuiControl</b>.
        </p>
    </topic>
</article>